WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:03.170
Nolan: All right.
Now turn right.

00:03.170 --> 00:04.338
[ Beep, camera shutter clicks ]

00:04.338 --> 00:05.672
Are you sure
you were born in March?

00:05.672 --> 00:08.592
Oh, I think she knows what month
she was born in.

00:08.592 --> 00:10.427
[ Slurring ]
Who are you, little one?

00:10.427 --> 00:13.013
Are you here of
your own free will,

00:13.013 --> 00:15.515
or are you a droid
locked in servitude?

00:15.515 --> 00:17.434
She doesn't even know
what planet she's on.

00:17.434 --> 00:19.520
Okay, that's fair.
But the state of California

00:19.520 --> 00:21.855
did require her to show
her birth certificate

00:21.855 --> 00:23.065
when she got
that driver's license.

00:23.065 --> 00:24.525
Yeah, yeah.
I'm just saying --

00:24.525 --> 00:27.110
You know, Pisces are normally
way too gentle

00:27.110 --> 00:29.488
to go on a drunken
vandalism spree.

00:29.488 --> 00:32.074
There's nothing normal about
the people we interact with.

00:32.074 --> 00:36.036
You are destined for more
than this, little one.

00:36.036 --> 00:39.122
Do you want to know a secret?

00:39.122 --> 00:42.459
I'm not really
Danielle Vonderclomp.

00:42.459 --> 00:45.629
My parents adopted me
from a Lithuanian orphanage

00:45.629 --> 00:47.172
when I was 2.

00:47.172 --> 00:50.300
My history,
shrouded in darkness.

00:50.300 --> 00:53.011
I believe that I am
secretly a princess

00:53.011 --> 00:56.890
destined to go back home
one day to rule.

00:56.890 --> 00:58.267
Okay, I'm sorry.

00:58.267 --> 01:00.018
Your Highness,
are you saying

01:00.018 --> 01:02.312
your parents just made up
a birthday for you?

01:02.312 --> 01:04.356
Well, duh.

01:04.356 --> 01:05.274
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh,
whoa, oh, oh ♪
Don't.

01:05.274 --> 01:06.358
I told you so.
Please don't.

01:06.358 --> 01:08.860
She's a Leo, for sure.
I said don't.

01:08.860 --> 01:12.781
♪ I'm gonna win for you
like I know you want me to do ♪

01:14.992 --> 01:17.160
Have you seen my hair tie?

01:17.160 --> 01:18.537
Nightstand.

01:18.537 --> 01:21.206
[ Scoffs ]
I swear I looked here.

01:21.206 --> 01:22.791
[ Sighs ]
So, today's the day?

01:22.791 --> 01:25.127
It is. And...?

01:25.127 --> 01:27.546
And...great.

01:28.964 --> 01:31.300
You think I'm going
back to work too soon?

01:31.300 --> 01:35.095
I voiced my opinion,
and I respect your decision.

01:35.095 --> 01:36.930
Right. It's just that...

01:36.930 --> 01:39.057
Well, technically,
you were dead.

01:39.057 --> 01:41.893
I mean, you were gone,
and they brought you back.

01:41.893 --> 01:43.437
I just think
maybe it might

01:43.437 --> 01:45.731
take you more than a week
to get past that.

01:45.731 --> 01:47.983
Yeah, but it's not like
that's the first time.

01:47.983 --> 01:50.736
Sure, but --
Whoa, wait. What?

01:50.736 --> 01:52.112
You've been dead before?

01:52.112 --> 01:53.530
Lopez: I knew
this was a bad idea.

01:53.530 --> 01:55.657
We should've used a service
to cover Justine's vacation.

01:55.657 --> 01:57.367
Your mom just wants
to spend more time with Jack.

01:57.367 --> 01:59.369
Why hire a temp nanny
when he's got family?

01:59.369 --> 02:01.705
Because a nanny
would be on time.

02:01.705 --> 02:04.333
[ Sighs ] I have to go.
Can you stay until she shows?

02:04.333 --> 02:06.168
Yeah. Go.

02:08.086 --> 02:09.296
[ Gasps ]

02:09.296 --> 02:10.047
Mami!

02:10.047 --> 02:11.131
Huh?

02:11.131 --> 02:12.549
Call 911!

02:12.549 --> 02:16.345
We should let Marshall
pick every restaurant

02:16.345 --> 02:18.513
for all
the sergeant's meetings.

02:18.513 --> 02:20.223
Did you try that
breakfast sandwich?

02:20.223 --> 02:22.434
No. Ashley's got me on
this Whole30 thing.

02:22.434 --> 02:23.560
No bread.

02:23.560 --> 02:26.063
Oh, you're missing out.
Hey, Smitty.

02:26.063 --> 02:27.356
Yeah, Sarge?

02:27.356 --> 02:29.566
You can't park your
personal vehicle in spots

02:29.566 --> 02:31.401
designated for marked units.

02:31.401 --> 02:34.655
The RV isn't my vehicle,
it's my house.

02:34.655 --> 02:37.491
#VanLife.

02:37.491 --> 02:39.534
You can't park your house
in marked spots either.

02:39.534 --> 02:43.580
♪♪

02:43.580 --> 02:45.040
Any chance he retires soon?

02:45.040 --> 02:47.042
You aren't that lucky.

02:47.042 --> 02:48.627
[ <i>Indistinct page</i>
<i>over intercom</i> ]

02:48.627 --> 02:50.796
Dr. Green: Okay.
She needs a couple stitches,

02:50.796 --> 02:52.339
and I'd like to admit her,

02:52.339 --> 02:55.008
get a CAT scan to make sure
nothing more serious presents.

02:55.008 --> 02:56.343
Of course.

02:56.343 --> 02:57.594
Thank you, Doctor.

02:57.594 --> 02:58.345
Are you single?

02:58.345 --> 02:59.596
Mom!

02:59.596 --> 03:00.889
Because I have four sons.

03:00.889 --> 03:02.307
One's a priest,

03:02.307 --> 03:05.102
but the others could use
a successful, young,

03:05.102 --> 03:07.020
beautiful woman
like yourself.

03:07.020 --> 03:08.855
That's sweet, but I'm engaged.

03:08.855 --> 03:11.149
Oh, congratulations.

03:11.149 --> 03:12.818
You let me know
if it doesn't work out.

03:12.818 --> 03:15.237
Sure thing. [ Chuckles ]

03:15.237 --> 03:17.114
Mom.

03:17.114 --> 03:18.865
I need you to tell me
what happened.
I'm fine.

03:18.865 --> 03:20.742
Where's my grandbaby?
At home with Wesley.

03:20.742 --> 03:22.202
Well, let's go see them.

03:22.202 --> 03:24.121
The doctors are overreacting.

03:24.121 --> 03:26.331
You're not leaving
until they clear you.

03:26.331 --> 03:29.084
I once worked an eight-hour
shift with a broken wrist.

03:29.084 --> 03:30.293
Last time I heard that story,

03:30.293 --> 03:32.462
it was a six-hour shift
with a sprain.

03:32.462 --> 03:34.714
Point is, I'm tougher
than I look.

03:34.714 --> 03:36.383
I know how tough you are,

03:36.383 --> 03:38.176
but I need you
to tell me what happened.

03:38.176 --> 03:39.010
Nothing.

03:41.263 --> 03:42.639
I don't want
to freak you out.

03:42.639 --> 03:44.641
I'm a cop.
Nothing freaks me out.
[ Sighs ]

03:44.641 --> 03:48.478
I was on my way to see you
when a big man grabbed me.

03:48.478 --> 03:51.273
I whacked him with my purse.
He threw me down.

03:51.273 --> 03:52.607
What aren't you telling me?

03:52.607 --> 03:53.400
Nothing.

03:55.735 --> 03:59.072
I'm sure
it's a misunderstanding.
Mom.

03:59.072 --> 04:01.616
"Tell your son
he's out of time."

04:01.616 --> 04:02.951
Out of time for what?

04:02.951 --> 04:04.327
I don't know.
That's all he said.

04:04.327 --> 04:06.204
Which son?
I don't know!

04:07.956 --> 04:10.584
It has to be
a misunderstanding.

04:10.584 --> 04:12.878
Your brothers
are all such good boys.

04:12.878 --> 04:15.088
My brothers used to
stuff me in a pillowcase

04:15.088 --> 04:16.339
and drag me around
the neighborhood.

04:16.339 --> 04:18.800
And look how tough
it made you.

04:18.800 --> 04:19.676
They did you a favor.

04:21.386 --> 04:24.264
What's with all these diets
Ashley has you on?

04:24.264 --> 04:25.682
Her dad's having
heart trouble.

04:25.682 --> 04:26.725
[ Glass shatters,
alarm blaring ]

04:26.725 --> 04:28.518
Burglary. 10:00.

04:28.518 --> 04:30.562
[ Tires screech ]

04:30.562 --> 04:32.814
Control, 7-Adam-100,
we got a burglary in progress.

04:32.814 --> 04:35.025
4-9-1-9-2 Figueroa.

04:35.025 --> 04:37.110
Send additional units.
[ Siren wails ]

04:37.110 --> 04:39.321
♪ I wish I was tornado, but
I guess I'm just some Play-Doh ♪

04:39.321 --> 04:41.323
Aaron: Hey! Show me your hands!
Foot pursuit. White adult male.

04:41.323 --> 04:43.241
Black hoodie,
jeans, headed south.

04:43.241 --> 04:44.993
♪ You told me I was pretty, but
that you could never touch me ♪

04:44.993 --> 04:47.746
♪ 'Cause to touch me would mean
you would have to feel ♪

04:47.746 --> 04:49.581
Get off of me!
♪ And I never felt so lucky ♪

04:49.581 --> 04:50.707
♪ When you said that
you could love me ♪
Aah! Oh!

04:50.707 --> 04:52.918
It's okay.
I got it, I got it.

04:52.918 --> 04:54.753
Are you all right?
[ Exhales sharply ]
Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

04:54.753 --> 04:56.087
Just, uh, tweaked my back
on the takedown.

04:56.087 --> 04:57.380
[ Handcuffs click ]

04:57.380 --> 04:59.216
Oh! [ Groans ]

04:59.216 --> 05:01.426
You're not fine.
You're in agony.
Oh!

05:01.426 --> 05:02.719
We're taking you
to the hospital.

05:02.719 --> 05:05.597
[ Groaning ]

05:05.597 --> 05:09.643
[ Siren wailing ]

05:09.643 --> 05:10.685
[ Tires screech ]

05:12.938 --> 05:15.273
What happened?

05:15.273 --> 05:17.609
He must have been going
at least 70.

05:17.609 --> 05:20.570
Lost control, hit a couple
parked cars, flipped.

05:20.570 --> 05:21.822
Several deep lacerations.

05:21.822 --> 05:23.406
Possible internal bleeding.

05:23.406 --> 05:25.492
Uh, don't move.

05:25.492 --> 05:27.285
Greg: It's stuck again.
Here. I'll pinch.

05:27.285 --> 05:28.078
You lift.

05:28.078 --> 05:31.164
[ Gurney creaks ]
Got it.

05:32.833 --> 05:34.626
...three, up!

05:34.626 --> 05:35.377
All right.

05:36.920 --> 05:37.712
Headed to Saint Stephen.

05:37.712 --> 05:38.964
All right.

05:41.174 --> 05:42.592
And what do we do next?

05:42.592 --> 05:44.469
We, uh, wait for backup
to secure the scene,

05:44.469 --> 05:46.555
then head to the hospital.
Why?

05:46.555 --> 05:48.974
Well, a death investigation
triggers different protocols.

05:48.974 --> 05:50.851
We go with the victim
in case he dies.

05:50.851 --> 05:52.143
Nicely done.

05:53.603 --> 05:54.646
Harper:
How's your mom?

05:54.646 --> 05:56.690
Okay, I think.

05:56.690 --> 05:59.442
She keeps going on about
how it was a misunderstanding.

05:59.442 --> 06:01.444
Uh, you think one of
your brothers is in trouble?

06:01.444 --> 06:03.154
It wouldn't be
the first time.

06:03.154 --> 06:04.739
If one of them is a reason
for Mom's attack,

06:04.739 --> 06:06.658
I will rain down
hell's own fury.

06:06.658 --> 06:09.160
Okay. So, technically,
this can't be your case.

06:09.160 --> 06:11.663
I know. It's your case.
I'm not even here.

06:11.663 --> 06:14.207
Good, because it's
a major conflict of interest

06:14.207 --> 06:16.501
for you to investigate
your own brothers.

06:16.501 --> 06:17.752
I know.
Plus, if I do it,

06:17.752 --> 06:18.628
I might end up
killing one of them.

06:18.628 --> 06:20.046
Huh.

06:20.046 --> 06:21.923
And here
they come now.

06:21.923 --> 06:24.634
That's Damian,
my oldest brother.

06:24.634 --> 06:27.512
Also known as Father Lopez
or Father D.

06:27.512 --> 06:29.347
Amen to that.

06:29.347 --> 06:30.932
He started a nonprofit
teaching job skills

06:30.932 --> 06:32.684
to former gang members,

06:32.684 --> 06:35.395
so he's got just as many friends
as he does enemies.

06:35.395 --> 06:37.856
And that's
Benjamin "Benny" Lopez.

06:37.856 --> 06:39.774
Second oldest.

06:39.774 --> 06:42.277
He was Gordon Gekko
for Halloween from
the time he was 3.

06:42.277 --> 06:44.654
When he was 12,
he opened an investment account

06:44.654 --> 06:46.114
using lawnmower earnings

06:46.114 --> 06:48.074
and our abuelita's
Social Security number.

06:48.074 --> 06:49.784
Her portfolio
is better than mine.

06:49.784 --> 06:52.412
And that's Cruz.
Middle child.

06:52.412 --> 06:54.164
In and out of rehab
since he was 18.

06:54.164 --> 06:56.708
Just can't seem
to get it together.

06:56.708 --> 06:59.252
When I became a cop, my mom made
me promise to never arrest him.

06:59.252 --> 07:00.837
I thought you had
four brothers.

07:00.837 --> 07:02.088
Bruno's the youngest,

07:02.088 --> 07:03.340
but he's been in New York
since college.

07:03.340 --> 07:05.008
I really don't think
he's involved.

07:05.008 --> 07:06.801
Angela,
what's going on?

07:06.801 --> 07:08.178
Mom's in the hospital.

07:08.178 --> 07:09.596
She okay?
Wait. What happened?

07:09.596 --> 07:10.847
Well, why didn't you have us
meet there?

07:10.847 --> 07:12.140
Your mother was
attacked this morning

07:12.140 --> 07:13.850
on her way
to Angela's house.

07:13.850 --> 07:15.518
She suffered
a blow to the head.

07:15.518 --> 07:16.978
The doctors are
running some tests.

07:16.978 --> 07:18.229
Who would attack Mom?

07:18.229 --> 07:19.356
Hold on.
Is that why we're here?

07:19.356 --> 07:21.149
What, you think
it's our fault?

07:21.149 --> 07:23.652
The assailant said, "Tell your
son he's running out of time."

07:23.652 --> 07:25.654
So, yeah, I think one of you
is at fault,

07:25.654 --> 07:27.781
and no one's leaving
until I get answers.

07:27.781 --> 07:30.158
All right, if one of you
wants to make this easy

07:30.158 --> 07:32.994
and just confess,
that would be awesome.

07:35.288 --> 07:37.332
All right, then.
Hard way it is.

07:38.583 --> 07:40.001
Come on.

07:40.001 --> 07:41.795
Really?

07:43.672 --> 07:45.840
[ Siren wailing ]

07:46.800 --> 07:48.259
What is this?

07:48.259 --> 07:51.388
♪♪

07:51.388 --> 07:53.431
I'm just gonna move you
real fast.

07:53.431 --> 07:55.684
[ Rob groaning ]

07:55.684 --> 07:57.560
That's an exit wound.

07:59.729 --> 08:01.606
Control, Engine 53.

08:01.606 --> 08:04.067
Advise Saint Stephen
we have a gunshot victim.

08:04.067 --> 08:07.112
ETA six minutes,
and advise PD we have a GSW.

08:07.112 --> 08:09.489
[ Gasps ]
Oh! Calm down, buddy.

08:09.489 --> 08:10.532
We're almost at
the hospital.
Oh!

08:10.532 --> 08:11.908
It's gonna be okay.

08:11.908 --> 08:13.576
[ Wailing continues ]

08:13.576 --> 08:19.040
♪♪

08:19.040 --> 08:21.000
[ Speaking
indistinctly ]

08:21.000 --> 08:22.877
[ Sighs ]
I thought I fixed it.

08:22.877 --> 08:24.212
It's fine.
You hold pressure.

08:24.212 --> 08:25.004
I'll go get
another gurney.

08:28.466 --> 08:31.886
[ Groaning ]

08:31.886 --> 08:34.013
♪♪

08:34.013 --> 08:35.557
[ Oxygen tank thuds ]
[ Grunts ]

08:35.557 --> 08:36.433
No!

08:36.433 --> 08:38.184
[ Greg groans ]

08:38.184 --> 08:47.694
♪♪

08:47.694 --> 08:56.953
♪♪

08:56.953 --> 09:06.504
♪♪

09:06.504 --> 09:07.505
Greg!

09:07.505 --> 09:12.302
♪♪

09:12.302 --> 09:13.762
What happened?

09:13.762 --> 09:15.722
Our patient must've
attacked him.
Why?

09:15.722 --> 09:18.641
I found a gunshot wound
when I was cleaning him up.

09:18.641 --> 09:19.726
He would know the hospital
would have to report

09:19.726 --> 09:21.978
that gunshot to the police.

09:21.978 --> 09:23.271
He's gone inside
the hospital.

09:23.271 --> 09:24.689
We need to
lock it down now.

09:30.612 --> 09:33.782
[ <i>Indistinct announcements</i>
<i>over intercom</i> ]

09:33.782 --> 09:35.116
Security guard.

09:35.116 --> 09:37.410
Hi. John Nolan.

09:37.410 --> 09:39.454
Jasper Lee.
Hospital's locked down.

09:39.454 --> 09:41.206
All incoming calls
are being rerouted.

09:41.206 --> 09:42.582
Okay, we're gonna have to
post up at all the exits,

09:42.582 --> 09:44.125
check everyone's I. D.
before they leave.

09:44.125 --> 09:45.460
Does that mean you've got
an I. D. on this guy?

09:45.460 --> 09:47.504
Rob Lukasey.
He left his wallet in the car.

09:47.504 --> 09:49.214
A laundry list
of priors.

09:49.214 --> 09:51.966
Uh, Celina, can you get him
a photo to distribute?
Will do.

09:51.966 --> 09:53.301
He's in
bad shape.

09:53.301 --> 09:55.303
His first priority will be
patching himself up.

09:55.303 --> 09:56.471
Well, we can put
extra security

09:56.471 --> 09:57.764
on the pharmacy
and storage rooms.

09:57.764 --> 09:59.808
But the truth is,

09:59.808 --> 10:01.351
there's medical supplies
everywhere in here.

10:01.351 --> 10:02.894
I got more officers
coming to help,

10:02.894 --> 10:03.853
but I'm sure I don't
have to tell you

10:03.853 --> 10:05.063
what a big job
this is gonna be.

10:05.063 --> 10:07.732
8 floors, 600 beds,
34 operating rooms.

10:07.732 --> 10:09.734
In our simulations,
a thorough search

10:09.734 --> 10:10.735
takes five hours.

10:10.735 --> 10:11.528
Hmm.
Well, let's get to it.

10:11.528 --> 10:12.737
Let's do it.

10:12.737 --> 10:13.947
Celina: Okay.

10:13.947 --> 10:15.657
Tim: Agh. Nolan.
[ Grunts ]

10:15.657 --> 10:16.741
You all right?

10:16.741 --> 10:17.867
Yeah, uh, fine.

10:17.867 --> 10:19.369
What -- What's
the lockdown status?

10:19.369 --> 10:21.287
Uh, we got, uh, everything
checked off the list, but --

10:21.287 --> 10:23.581
No, call Grey and tell him
Tim is not here as a supervisor.

10:23.581 --> 10:24.874
He's here as a patient.

10:24.874 --> 10:27.502
I told you,
I'm fine. Agh!
Oh, my God.

10:27.502 --> 10:28.920
Ohh, okay.

10:28.920 --> 10:30.463
Okay, I'm not fine.

10:30.463 --> 10:31.673
Get me a doctor.

10:33.591 --> 10:35.885
"Tell your son
he's out of time."

10:35.885 --> 10:37.303
Any idea what that means?

10:37.303 --> 10:40.098
No. No. If I did,
I would tell you.

10:40.098 --> 10:42.851
Ask him
about his record.

10:42.851 --> 10:44.769
<i>I was getting to that.</i>

10:44.769 --> 10:47.188
<i>So, you got a couple arrests</i>
<i>for public intoxication</i>

10:47.188 --> 10:50.233
and multiple DUIs.
Ancient history.

10:50.233 --> 10:52.986
I've been sober for one year
and 47 days today.

10:52.986 --> 10:54.070
[ Door opens ]

10:54.070 --> 10:56.406
Whoa.
What are you doing here?

10:56.406 --> 10:58.032
I'm representing
my client.

10:59.534 --> 11:00.660
What?

11:00.660 --> 11:02.537
Hey, Ange.

11:02.537 --> 11:05.456
You're not even
a defense attorney anymore.
Look, I know.

11:05.456 --> 11:07.250
This is my chance to get <i>one</i>
of your brothers to like me.

11:07.250 --> 11:08.835
They're never
gonna like you.

11:08.835 --> 11:10.587
Objection --
argumentative.

11:10.587 --> 11:12.755
Your mother-in-law is
in the hospital right now

11:12.755 --> 11:14.716
because of him.
Objection --
speculation.

11:14.716 --> 11:16.134
All right. Enough.

11:16.134 --> 11:17.260
You, sit down.
Yeah.

11:17.260 --> 11:18.970
You, go back inside.

11:18.970 --> 11:19.762
All right.

11:19.762 --> 11:23.558
♪♪

11:23.558 --> 11:24.559
That was dope.
Yeah.

11:24.559 --> 11:25.977
Can we get back on track?

11:25.977 --> 11:27.187
-Mm-hmm.
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

11:27.187 --> 11:28.605
Look, I've been trying
to tell you,

11:28.605 --> 11:30.982
that last DUI was the best thing
to happen to me.

11:30.982 --> 11:32.609
I've been clean and sober
ever since.

11:32.609 --> 11:35.403
I understand you work with
a lot of ex-cons.

11:35.403 --> 11:37.822
Guilt by association.
Really, Detective?

11:37.822 --> 11:39.657
[ Chuckles ]
It's all right.

11:39.657 --> 11:41.910
My mission is to help people
get out of the gang life.

11:41.910 --> 11:44.871
What if one of the gangs
got tired of you interfering

11:44.871 --> 11:46.873
and decided
to send a message?

11:46.873 --> 11:49.209
By attacking my mother?

11:49.209 --> 11:51.252
No.

11:51.252 --> 11:53.213
The people
that I work with,

11:53.213 --> 11:54.339
they might not
always agree with me,

11:54.339 --> 11:57.258
but they respect
the collar.

11:57.258 --> 11:59.469
Even if they didn't,
they know my sister's a cop.

11:59.469 --> 12:00.637
<i>So if it's</i> not
<i>because of you,</i>

12:00.637 --> 12:03.264
which brother do you think
I should be focused on?

12:03.264 --> 12:04.682
Cruz, Clearly.
[ Cellphone chimes ]

12:04.682 --> 12:06.434
Uh, sorry.

12:06.434 --> 12:10.730
I just need to
respond to this.
[ Keypad clacking ]

12:10.730 --> 12:11.814
[ Exhales ]
[ Cellphone swooshes ]

12:11.814 --> 12:13.316
As I was saying --
[ Cellphone chimes ]

12:13.316 --> 12:15.109
♪♪

12:15.109 --> 12:16.861
[ Cellphone chimes, clicks ]

12:16.861 --> 12:18.363
A thousand apologies.
Uh -- [ Laughs ]

12:18.363 --> 12:20.907
[ Chiming continues ]

12:20.907 --> 12:23.076
[ Chuckles ]
It never ends. Uh...

12:23.076 --> 12:24.702
[ Cellphone chimes, swooshes ]

12:24.702 --> 12:26.329
Sorry.
No, you're not.

12:26.329 --> 12:29.999
Uh, what exactly is
your business, Mr. Lopez?

12:29.999 --> 12:31.584
Um...
[ Cellphone chimes ]

12:31.584 --> 12:33.211
-I --
-Okay.

12:33.211 --> 12:34.629
♪♪

12:34.629 --> 12:36.214
Hey,
while I have you here,

12:36.214 --> 12:38.466
Angela's been
dragging her feet.

12:38.466 --> 12:39.842
We really gotta get
baby Jack baptized.

12:39.842 --> 12:41.803
No, you know, I just --

12:41.803 --> 12:44.264
I don't really want to
get in the middle of --
of what you guys have --

12:44.264 --> 12:46.266
Well, I know.
I know you're not Catholic.

12:46.266 --> 12:47.558
What's your
denomination?

12:47.558 --> 12:48.685
[ Pops mouth ]

12:48.685 --> 12:51.521
Protestant?

12:51.521 --> 12:52.647
I don't know.
Is that even an option?

12:52.647 --> 12:53.898
No.

12:53.898 --> 12:55.525
Oh.

12:55.525 --> 12:57.277
I'm gonna go
with Episcopalian.
Sure.

12:57.277 --> 12:58.987
Look, I get it.
Your line of work,

12:58.987 --> 13:01.239
there is
a lot of money at stake.

13:01.239 --> 13:03.825
Might drive a person
to violence.

13:03.825 --> 13:06.452
The guys I work with,
they're not gonna
beat up someone's mom.

13:06.452 --> 13:08.788
That's too kind.

13:08.788 --> 13:11.040
They'll just sue you
to death.

13:11.040 --> 13:13.251
[ Cellphone chimes ]

13:13.251 --> 13:15.169
Can I just answer
that one --
Mnh-mnh.

13:16.212 --> 13:18.006
Ask him about
his credit report.

13:18.006 --> 13:21.134
I was getting to that.

13:21.134 --> 13:23.344
So, we ran
your credit report,

13:23.344 --> 13:25.555
and we saw that
you took out a $15,000 loan.

13:25.555 --> 13:27.223
You wanna tell us
about that?

13:27.223 --> 13:28.391
You don't have to
answer that.

13:28.391 --> 13:30.351
Yes, he does.

13:30.351 --> 13:32.603
<i>The loan is for</i>
<i>college classes.</i>

13:32.603 --> 13:34.439
<i>I'm getting my bachelor's</i>
<i>in accounting.</i>

13:34.439 --> 13:35.815
I didn't want to
say anything in case

13:35.815 --> 13:37.233
I couldn't hack it

13:37.233 --> 13:40.069
because I know
what you think of me.

13:40.069 --> 13:41.779
<i>And I know</i>
<i>I screwed up a lot.</i>

13:41.779 --> 13:43.197
I know you have no reason
to trust me.

13:43.197 --> 13:46.075
But whatever's going on,
it's not me.

13:47.952 --> 13:49.829
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:49.829 --> 13:52.081
Man: [ Over radio ]
<i>Clear on floor two.</i>

13:52.081 --> 13:54.417
Floor three clear.
Heading to four.

13:54.417 --> 13:56.210
Okay. Thank you.

13:56.210 --> 13:58.713
Well, our suspect
killed a woman this morning.

13:58.713 --> 14:00.339
Home invasion
in West Hollywood.

14:00.339 --> 14:02.341
The victim's husband
managed to get the gun

14:02.341 --> 14:04.677
away from the suspect
and shoot him as he escaped.

14:04.677 --> 14:06.679
Okay, so he's looking at
life in prison if we catch him.

14:06.679 --> 14:08.473
<i>When</i> we catch him.

14:08.473 --> 14:10.016
God, I hate hospitals.

14:10.016 --> 14:10.975
Doesn't everyone?

14:10.975 --> 14:12.643
Yeah, I guess.

14:12.643 --> 14:13.811
Hey.
How's your partner?

14:13.811 --> 14:15.354
Shattered cheekbone.

14:15.354 --> 14:16.814
Plastic surgeon's
on his way in.

14:16.814 --> 14:18.107
You're going
back to work?

14:18.107 --> 14:19.609
I'll wait until he's
out of surgery.
Right.

14:19.609 --> 14:20.902
I just found out
this morning

14:20.902 --> 14:22.612
Bailey has been dead
more than once.

14:22.612 --> 14:24.280
I know.

14:24.280 --> 14:25.698
I felt it when
I first met her.

14:25.698 --> 14:28.117
One had something to do with,
uh, flying?

14:28.117 --> 14:29.952
Wow. Yeah.

14:29.952 --> 14:31.788
A-A-A halo jump
went sideways.

14:31.788 --> 14:34.707
♪♪

14:34.707 --> 14:36.793
This is Nolan,
fourth floor west.

14:36.793 --> 14:38.878
We just found
the suspect's bloody clothes.

14:38.878 --> 14:41.464
Looks like he tried to patch
himself up best he could.

14:41.464 --> 14:43.466
Right, and then changed
into some scrubs.

14:43.466 --> 14:46.094
He'll still need an I. D.
in order to exit the building.

14:46.094 --> 14:47.428
Well, if he can break
into a house,

14:47.428 --> 14:49.305
he can steal
a staff I. D.

14:50.848 --> 14:52.183
I'll run down
all the gang members

14:52.183 --> 14:54.894
who work for
Father Lopez.

14:54.894 --> 14:57.271
Cruz agreed to
a drug test,

14:57.271 --> 14:59.649
so we should have those results
in a couple hours.

14:59.649 --> 15:02.110
For the first time in his life,
I actually think he's innocent.

15:02.110 --> 15:03.653
I've always been
so hard on him.

15:03.653 --> 15:04.946
Maybe if I had been
more supportive,

15:04.946 --> 15:07.323
he would have
gotten clean sooner.
You know better.

15:07.323 --> 15:09.158
Addicts only get clean
when they are ready.

15:09.158 --> 15:10.785
[ Door opens ]

15:11.786 --> 15:13.621
Oh. There you are.

15:13.621 --> 15:14.914
Uh, you okay?

15:14.914 --> 15:17.333
You're looking
a little shiny.
Yeah.

15:17.333 --> 15:19.544
Yeah, I'm -- I'm fine.
I just feel a little warm.

15:19.544 --> 15:21.963
Look, I thought you should know,
hospital's locked down

15:21.963 --> 15:24.215
while they search
for a homicide suspect.

15:24.215 --> 15:25.591
I'm heading over
to supervise.

15:25.591 --> 15:27.760
There's a killer in the hospital
with my mother?

15:27.760 --> 15:30.012
Relax. She's fine.

15:30.012 --> 15:31.472
I assigned Thorsen
to watch her door.

15:32.890 --> 15:35.017
Hi, ma'am.
I'm Officer Aaron Thorsen.
Hm?

15:35.017 --> 15:36.352
I've been assigned
to keep you safe,

15:36.352 --> 15:37.311
and I just want
to let you know

15:37.311 --> 15:38.729
that there's nothing
to worry about.

15:38.729 --> 15:40.690
You are handsome.

15:42.650 --> 15:43.901
Thank you.

15:43.901 --> 15:46.028
Do you have any sisters?

15:46.028 --> 15:47.488
No, I'm an only child.
Cousins?

15:48.990 --> 15:52.702
My second eldest son, Benny,
he is successful, sweet,

15:52.702 --> 15:54.162
goes to church on Sundays.
Mm.

15:54.162 --> 15:56.581
But he needs a woman
to settle down with.

15:56.581 --> 15:59.542
Are you asking me to set up one
of my cousins with your son?
Mm-hmm.

15:59.542 --> 16:03.880
And in return, I will set you up
with my niece, Isabella.

16:03.880 --> 16:05.256
She's a professional
dancer.

16:07.175 --> 16:09.177
You got a picture?
Mm-hmm.

16:11.888 --> 16:13.890
Oh, yeah.
Mm-hmm.
[ Laughs ]

16:15.433 --> 16:17.018
It's probably
just a muscle spasm.

16:17.018 --> 16:17.810
You didn't have
to clock out.

16:17.810 --> 16:19.353
Of course I did.

16:19.353 --> 16:22.732
Oh, hey. I'm just
searching for bad guys.

16:22.732 --> 16:24.609
All clear here.

16:24.609 --> 16:26.611
Wait, so Nolan's leaving
someone on every floor?

16:26.611 --> 16:29.071
Yes. We've been cops
for more than 10 seconds.

16:29.071 --> 16:30.406
We can handle this.

16:30.406 --> 16:32.366
Hey, Doc,
what's the word?

16:32.366 --> 16:34.410
When we took that bullet out
a few years back,

16:34.410 --> 16:37.038
there was a-a fragment that was
too complicated to remove.

16:37.038 --> 16:39.123
I remember.
Bullet?

16:39.123 --> 16:41.459
I was shot.
It wasn't a big deal.

16:41.459 --> 16:43.628
I saved his life
first day on the job.

16:43.628 --> 16:45.171
It was a <i>huge</i> deal.

16:45.171 --> 16:46.964
Back to the fragment.

16:46.964 --> 16:49.383
The pain you're experiencing
is because the fragment

16:49.383 --> 16:51.177
has migrated closer
to your spinal column

16:51.177 --> 16:53.262
and is pressing up
against a nerve.

16:53.262 --> 16:54.889
We'll need to do surgery
to remove it.

16:54.889 --> 16:57.266
Okay.
Uh, when?

16:57.266 --> 16:59.644
Well, I mean, hold on.
Wh-What are the risks?

17:01.020 --> 17:03.564
Well, we are talking about
the spine, so...

17:03.564 --> 17:04.690
yes, it's risky.

17:04.690 --> 17:06.442
But it's laparoscopic.

17:06.442 --> 17:08.486
So if all goes well,
he'll be home by dinner.

17:08.486 --> 17:09.487
If?

17:09.487 --> 17:10.863
I know it's scary,

17:10.863 --> 17:13.074
but leaving the fragment
in place is much riskier.

17:13.074 --> 17:14.700
Well,
then we do surgery.

17:14.700 --> 17:15.910
Thank you.

17:21.123 --> 17:22.959
Uh...

17:22.959 --> 17:25.127
I'm gonna get back
to the search.

17:29.298 --> 17:31.217
South wing is clear.
Headed to north.

17:31.217 --> 17:32.009
[ Elevator bell dings ]

17:34.720 --> 17:36.889
Sir. Are you...?

17:36.889 --> 17:38.975
Oh, my -- Oh!

17:38.975 --> 17:40.476
I -- I need help
over here!

17:46.274 --> 17:48.192
Ah, good thing I was
on the Whole30 diet.

17:48.192 --> 17:50.319
That food poisoning
is no joke.

17:50.319 --> 17:52.446
[ Groaning ]

17:52.446 --> 17:54.657
Marshall can never pick
the breakfast place again.

17:54.657 --> 17:55.658
Never.

17:55.658 --> 17:56.867
[ Groans ]
Oh, no.

17:56.867 --> 17:57.994
This is kind of fun.

17:57.994 --> 17:58.869
It's like a sleepover.

17:58.869 --> 18:00.746
[ Groans ]
Oh, God.

18:00.746 --> 18:02.123
Should I call the nurse?

18:02.123 --> 18:03.791
No, no, no,
no, no, no, no.

18:03.791 --> 18:06.377
You need to get back
to the station immediately.
What?

18:06.377 --> 18:07.587
What? Why?

18:07.587 --> 18:10.339
Because if we're both
out of commission...

18:10.339 --> 18:11.966
Based on seniority...

18:11.966 --> 18:13.426
Smitty's in charge.

18:14.969 --> 18:16.429
Oh.
Yeah.
You're still
standing there.

18:16.429 --> 18:18.139
Go.
Yeah.

18:18.139 --> 18:19.473
Hey, man.
All right, bro.

18:19.473 --> 18:25.021
♪♪

18:25.021 --> 18:26.522
Smitty.
Smitty!

18:26.522 --> 18:28.357
Hey!
Wha-- What's going on?

18:28.357 --> 18:29.984
Acting Sergeant Smitty.

18:29.984 --> 18:31.944
Right. Why is Casey Curtis
leaving the station?

18:31.944 --> 18:33.321
End of shift time off.

18:33.321 --> 18:34.780
When you're in charge,

18:34.780 --> 18:36.616
you can let all your friends
go home early.

18:36.616 --> 18:38.159
But we're short today.

18:38.159 --> 18:39.160
You know how many units
are attached

18:39.160 --> 18:39.994
to the hospital event,
right?

18:39.994 --> 18:41.537
Self-care is important.

18:41.537 --> 18:43.039
Smitty --
[ Tires screech ]

18:43.039 --> 18:44.123
[ <i>Car bass thumping</i> ]

18:44.123 --> 18:45.958
-Get out!
-All right!

18:45.958 --> 18:47.335
Lucy: What the hell
is going on?

18:47.335 --> 18:48.961
We caught the guy who beat up
Father Lopez's mother.

18:50.963 --> 18:53.549
We heard what happened
to your mom and wanted to help.

18:53.549 --> 18:55.092
So you abducted a man?

18:55.092 --> 18:56.802
It was
a citizen's arrest.

18:56.802 --> 18:58.554
On what evidence?

18:58.554 --> 19:00.640
He's been talkin' smack about
Father Lopez for weeks!

19:00.640 --> 19:01.932
The whole hood
heard him.

19:01.932 --> 19:04.018
He's lucky
that's all I did.

19:04.018 --> 19:05.603
Hypocrite's sleeping
with my wife.

19:07.688 --> 19:09.482
With me, now.

19:14.320 --> 19:16.864
[ Cell door slams ]

19:16.864 --> 19:18.866
You're sleeping
with his wife?

19:18.866 --> 19:19.700
You're a priest.

19:19.700 --> 19:20.868
I know.

19:23.496 --> 19:25.039
I know.

19:26.666 --> 19:28.834
Been struggling
with my vows recently.

19:28.834 --> 19:30.503
Are you kidding me?

19:30.503 --> 19:33.464
Jumping to adultery
is more than just struggling.

19:33.464 --> 19:36.717
We all fall short
of the glory of God.

19:36.717 --> 19:39.679
But I really don't think Carmody
had anything to do with Mom.

19:39.679 --> 19:42.014
[ Sighs ]

19:42.014 --> 19:43.599
I have to look into it.

19:43.599 --> 19:46.394
You never know
what people are capable of.

19:46.394 --> 19:48.062
I didn't know you were
capable of this.

19:50.690 --> 19:52.066
[ Buzzer sounds ]

19:54.902 --> 19:56.278
Ashley: You know,
with your injury,

19:56.278 --> 19:58.656
you could retire right now
if you wanted.

19:58.656 --> 20:01.367
She's right.

20:01.367 --> 20:02.451
Are you trying
to get rid of me?

20:02.451 --> 20:05.538
It's not a crazy idea.

20:05.538 --> 20:08.541
My dad waited too long
to call it quits.

20:08.541 --> 20:10.501
He can't do any of
the things he planned on.

20:10.501 --> 20:12.461
It's a good deal.

20:12.461 --> 20:17.633
Disability pay is the average of
your last three years of income,

20:17.633 --> 20:21.637
50% salary plus overtime.

20:21.637 --> 20:24.014
That's about 60%
of your current take home.

20:24.014 --> 20:25.433
And that's tax free,
right?

20:25.433 --> 20:27.017
Yes, it is.

20:27.017 --> 20:29.311
Plus, my dad gets
a cost-of-living adjustment.

20:29.311 --> 20:33.023
That's a 3% raise every year,
for life.

20:33.023 --> 20:35.151
I never really
did the math before.

20:35.151 --> 20:38.654
Just think.
We both love to travel.

20:38.654 --> 20:41.240
I always did want to see a game
at every Major League stadium.

20:41.240 --> 20:44.326
W-We could even
move out of L. A.

20:44.326 --> 20:46.370
I mean, I can be
a lifeguard anywhere.

20:46.370 --> 20:47.455
Right? So long
as there's a beach.

20:48.664 --> 20:51.041
I hear Bali has
a bunch of those.

20:51.041 --> 20:52.626
That's true.

20:52.626 --> 20:54.253
This is so exciting.

20:54.253 --> 20:55.671
No, I haven't
decided anything.

20:55.671 --> 20:58.174
No, I know, but...

20:58.174 --> 21:00.050
Free money?

21:00.050 --> 21:01.552
You'd be crazy
not to, right?

21:01.552 --> 21:03.053
Hm.

21:05.347 --> 21:07.767
Anybody else hungry?

21:10.102 --> 21:12.062
Probably not the best time,
right?

21:12.062 --> 21:13.606
I'll pass.

21:13.606 --> 21:17.026
I'm just gonna grab something
from the cafeteria.

21:17.026 --> 21:17.818
[ Softly ] Bye.

21:19.779 --> 21:21.572
Just think about it.

21:21.572 --> 21:23.032
Okay.

21:23.032 --> 21:26.619
[ Exhales deeply ]

21:26.619 --> 21:28.871
Woman: Have they
been assessed yet?
[ Indistinct conversations ]

21:28.871 --> 21:33.375
♪♪

21:33.375 --> 21:35.961
Here's the thing.
Melody -- she's wonderful.

21:35.961 --> 21:37.546
I love her to death.
She's my favorite cousin.

21:37.546 --> 21:39.006
But?

21:39.006 --> 21:41.342
But I-I don't think
she's right for Cruz.

21:41.342 --> 21:42.551
You know, he needs
someone who's solid

21:42.551 --> 21:43.844
and is gonna call him
on his B. S.

21:43.844 --> 21:45.721
You're thinking Tara.

21:45.721 --> 21:46.931
You're not wrong.

21:46.931 --> 21:48.641
[ Cellphone chimes ]

21:48.641 --> 21:52.019
Okay, Angela just sent me
a photo of this guy Carmody.

21:52.019 --> 21:53.145
Is this the man
that attacked you?

21:53.145 --> 21:54.188
No.

21:54.188 --> 21:55.272
No?
Mnh-mnh.

21:55.272 --> 21:56.148
Oh.

21:58.609 --> 22:00.611
Okay, I told her that they're
gonna be releasing you soon,

22:00.611 --> 22:02.696
so she should be
on her way.

22:02.696 --> 22:04.824
Oh, hey, did you set up
Wesley and Lopez?

22:04.824 --> 22:07.159
[ Laughs ] No.
She never needed my help.

22:07.159 --> 22:09.578
She was born
knowing her own mind.

22:09.578 --> 22:11.664
Yeah, that sounds like Lopez.
[ Chuckles ]

22:11.664 --> 22:13.415
♪♪

22:13.415 --> 22:14.792
Can I see Isabella
one more time?

22:14.792 --> 22:16.001
Mm-hmm.
Yeah.

22:17.628 --> 22:19.755
Wow!
Yeah, I'm telling you.

22:19.755 --> 22:20.506
Very flexible.

22:22.550 --> 22:24.301
Clear.

22:24.301 --> 22:27.179
You know, cops spend an awful
lot of time in hospitals.

22:27.179 --> 22:28.347
Whatever
your aversion is,

22:28.347 --> 22:29.265
you're gonna have to
deal with it.

22:29.265 --> 22:30.808
I know.

22:30.808 --> 22:33.185
I have to ask --
You don't see dead people?

22:33.185 --> 22:35.062
[ Chuckles ] No.

22:35.062 --> 22:36.814
I mean, who doesn't feel
a presence from time to time?

22:36.814 --> 22:38.023
Me.

22:38.023 --> 22:38.899
Most everyone I know.

22:38.899 --> 22:40.067
Yeah,
but I'm not crazy.

22:40.067 --> 22:42.653
I don't see dead people.
Good.

22:42.653 --> 22:46.407
It's just that hospitals
remind me of my sister.

22:46.407 --> 22:48.325
When they found her,
she was in bad shape.

22:48.325 --> 22:51.787
She, uh,
held out for two weeks,

22:51.787 --> 22:53.831
and I visited every day.

22:53.831 --> 22:55.082
I'm sorry.

22:57.668 --> 22:58.419
Next floor?

22:58.419 --> 22:59.837
Yeah.

22:59.837 --> 23:05.467
♪♪

23:05.467 --> 23:06.719
[ Bed whirs ]

23:06.719 --> 23:07.761
[ Sighs ]

23:10.556 --> 23:12.558
She's one of the best
surgeons in the country.

23:15.269 --> 23:16.520
I'm not worried.

23:16.520 --> 23:18.397
It's okay if you are.

23:18.397 --> 23:21.734
Eh, it's just a little
spinal surgery, you know?

23:21.734 --> 23:23.152
Might be fine.

23:23.152 --> 23:25.362
Might be
paralyzed for life.

23:25.362 --> 23:27.781
Excited to find out which.

23:27.781 --> 23:31.327
[ Sighs ] I'm gonna go stretch
my legs while I still can.

23:31.327 --> 23:32.536
Agh.

23:32.536 --> 23:33.996
That's the spirit.

23:33.996 --> 23:35.122
[ Sighs ]

23:40.085 --> 23:42.880
[ Indistinct conversations,
telephones ringing ]

23:45.299 --> 23:46.842
Mm.

23:53.015 --> 23:55.935
♪♪

23:55.935 --> 23:58.270
-Hey.
-Hey.

23:58.270 --> 24:01.357
♪♪

24:01.357 --> 24:03.567
[ Both grunting ]

24:03.567 --> 24:05.569
[ Clattering ]

24:05.569 --> 24:08.530
♪♪

24:08.530 --> 24:10.449
Agh.
Agh!

24:10.449 --> 24:11.450
Agh!

24:11.450 --> 24:12.493
[ Tim groans ]

24:12.493 --> 24:14.453
♪♪

24:14.453 --> 24:15.454
[ Grunts ]

24:15.454 --> 24:18.582
♪♪

24:18.582 --> 24:19.541
It was the shooter.

24:19.541 --> 24:21.085
Don't try to move.
I can't.

24:21.085 --> 24:22.628
What happened?

24:22.628 --> 24:24.296
The fragment must've shifted
towards Tim's spinal cord,

24:24.296 --> 24:25.631
and that's what's causing
his paralysis.

24:25.631 --> 24:27.466
Can you tell my sister,
please?

24:27.466 --> 24:28.842
Sure.

24:30.427 --> 24:32.638
Hey, do not tell Chen.

24:32.638 --> 24:34.056
She's got enough
on her plate.

24:34.056 --> 24:36.433
We need to get you
into surgery stat.

24:36.433 --> 24:37.267
Agh!

24:42.856 --> 24:44.191
[ Elevator bell dings ]

24:44.191 --> 24:47.653
♪♪

24:47.653 --> 24:49.113
If you two
hit it off...
Mm-hmm.

24:49.113 --> 24:51.240
...I expect you to name
your firstborn after me.

24:51.240 --> 24:53.409
[ Chuckles ]
Okay, that's a deal.

24:53.409 --> 24:55.786
Mom, are you setting up Aaron?
Yes.

24:55.786 --> 24:58.205
Don't you think he'd be perfect
for Isabella?

24:58.205 --> 25:00.624
Izzie's way out of his league.
No offense.

25:00.624 --> 25:02.418
No, I agree.

25:02.418 --> 25:04.128
Any news on Tim?
No.

25:04.128 --> 25:05.587
He's still in surgery
for about two more hours.

25:05.587 --> 25:06.588
Oh.

25:06.588 --> 25:07.965
Go join the manhunt.

25:07.965 --> 25:09.216
Okay.

25:11.427 --> 25:13.470
Your brothers texted me

25:13.470 --> 25:15.222
to say you interrogated them
at the station

25:15.222 --> 25:17.057
like common criminals.

25:17.057 --> 25:19.059
You know I don't like it when
you fight with your brothers.

25:19.059 --> 25:20.936
Mom,
you were assaulted.

25:20.936 --> 25:22.604
Aw.
You're lucky you're okay.

25:22.604 --> 25:25.024
But one of your sons
is in serious danger.

25:25.024 --> 25:26.442
And if there's something
you're not telling me,

25:26.442 --> 25:27.651
you're not
protecting them.

25:27.651 --> 25:28.902
You're leaving them
at risk.

25:28.902 --> 25:30.112
I told you everything.

25:30.112 --> 25:31.155
Tell me again.

25:33.115 --> 25:36.118
I went outside to wait
for my rideshare.

25:36.118 --> 25:38.078
Out of nowhere,
a man attacked me.

25:38.078 --> 25:39.538
I hit him
with my purse.

25:39.538 --> 25:41.707
He said,
"Tell your son" --
Back up.

25:41.707 --> 25:43.709
Rideshare?
What happened to your car?

25:43.709 --> 25:44.835
I gave it to Benny.

25:44.835 --> 25:46.295
What do you mean,
you gave it to Benny?

25:46.295 --> 25:47.796
He said he needed it.

25:47.796 --> 25:49.256
I didn't ask.

25:49.256 --> 25:51.091
[ Cellphone clicks, beeps ]

25:51.091 --> 25:53.844
[ Dialing ]
<i>You've reached Benjamin Lopez.</i>

25:53.844 --> 25:56.013
<i>Leave a message.</i>
[ Sighs ]

25:57.056 --> 25:58.807
[ Dialing ]

25:58.807 --> 26:00.851
Hey, how's Tim?

26:00.851 --> 26:02.019
Still in surgery.

26:02.019 --> 26:03.395
Is Benny still
at the station?

26:03.395 --> 26:04.897
No. He went to work.
Why?

26:04.897 --> 26:06.940
He lied.
He's having money problems.

26:06.940 --> 26:08.358
<i>I tried to call him,</i>
<i>but he's not answering.</i>

26:08.358 --> 26:09.777
We ran
his credit report.

26:09.777 --> 26:11.487
We didn't see
any outstanding loans.

26:11.487 --> 26:13.405
An enforcer
going after family?

26:13.405 --> 26:16.116
That's off-the-books debt.
He's into a loan shark.

26:16.116 --> 26:17.951
We need to find him
so I can kill him

26:17.951 --> 26:19.620
before
somebody else does.

26:19.620 --> 26:20.704
[ Indistinct conversations ]

26:20.704 --> 26:22.706
Jan.

26:22.706 --> 26:24.041
Where's everybody going?

26:24.041 --> 26:25.084
Pool party
at Mario's.

26:25.084 --> 26:26.668
No...
[ Scoffs ] No.

26:26.668 --> 26:27.961
Uh, we don't have
the staff for that.

26:27.961 --> 26:29.296
Y-You have to stay.

26:29.296 --> 26:32.549
Well, Acting Sergeant Smitty
says we don't.

26:32.549 --> 26:34.343
[ Exhales sharply ]

26:34.343 --> 26:35.135
[ Stammers ]

26:35.135 --> 26:36.720
Oh. Can you
talk to them?

26:36.720 --> 26:38.722
I believe it was Tim and Grey
who sent <i>you</i> back

26:38.722 --> 26:40.015
to rein in Smitty.

26:40.015 --> 26:41.391
They don't respect me,
but --

26:41.391 --> 26:43.435
What are you talking about?
You just saw. I --

26:43.435 --> 26:45.687
Yeah, that's because
Smitty told them to go home.

26:45.687 --> 26:47.773
You just have to tell them
something different.

26:47.773 --> 26:49.399
[ Stammers ]
Hey.

26:49.399 --> 26:51.193
After everything
you have been through,

26:51.193 --> 26:53.529
how often you
have proven yourself,

26:53.529 --> 26:55.656
there is not a cop in here
who would not have your back

26:55.656 --> 26:57.491
if you asked.

26:57.491 --> 26:59.409
♪♪

26:59.409 --> 27:01.829
Uh, hey, guys,
listen up.

27:01.829 --> 27:03.705
I need your help.

27:03.705 --> 27:05.124
We have two sergeants
out of commission

27:05.124 --> 27:06.291
in the hospital
right now

27:06.291 --> 27:07.876
and a murder suspect
on the loose.

27:07.876 --> 27:10.295
That search has us
spread pretty thin.

27:10.295 --> 27:12.256
We need all hands on deck
right now.

27:12.256 --> 27:14.133
I'm sorry,
but the pool party,

27:14.133 --> 27:15.217
it has to wait.

27:15.217 --> 27:18.595
♪♪

27:18.595 --> 27:20.722
You got it, Chen.
Man: All right.

27:20.722 --> 27:21.932
Let's go, guys.

27:21.932 --> 27:23.267
Woman: She needs us.
You heard her.

27:23.267 --> 27:25.519
Thank you, thank you.

27:25.519 --> 27:27.187
Thank you!

27:27.187 --> 27:29.565
So, does this mean
you're in charge now?

27:29.565 --> 27:31.149
♪♪

27:31.149 --> 27:33.068
Yeah, I guess so.

27:33.068 --> 27:35.779
Cool.
I'll be in the breakroom.

27:35.779 --> 27:38.699
Being in charge
is exhausting.

27:38.699 --> 27:42.870
♪♪

27:42.870 --> 27:47.291
♪♪

27:47.291 --> 27:48.292
Nolan!

27:48.292 --> 27:52.254
♪♪

27:52.254 --> 27:54.923
He cut the wire so the alarm
wouldn't go off.

27:54.923 --> 27:57.050
Nice catch.
I'll cover.

27:57.050 --> 28:02.514
♪♪

28:02.514 --> 28:04.016
I see blood.

28:04.016 --> 28:10.188
♪♪

28:10.188 --> 28:11.690
Should we split up?

28:11.690 --> 28:13.108
Well,
proper procedure says

28:13.108 --> 28:15.110
we stay within
40 feet of each other,

28:15.110 --> 28:16.236
hearing distance,

28:16.236 --> 28:17.988
just in case
anything goes wrong.

28:17.988 --> 28:19.072
If you'd rather
stick together --

28:19.072 --> 28:20.824
No. I can handle it.

28:20.824 --> 28:22.159
We got to find
this guy fast.

28:22.159 --> 28:23.452
All right.

28:23.452 --> 28:24.786
I'll go left.
You go right.

28:24.786 --> 28:25.829
We'll meet up back here.

28:25.829 --> 28:27.623
Copy.

28:27.623 --> 28:34.129
♪♪

28:34.129 --> 28:40.677
♪♪

28:40.677 --> 28:42.012
[ Gate creaks ]

28:42.012 --> 28:49.686
♪♪

28:49.686 --> 28:57.569
♪♪

28:57.569 --> 28:58.987
Jasper.
[ Gun cocks ]

28:58.987 --> 29:02.115
Not a sound,
or I'll blow your head off.

29:06.745 --> 29:15.545
♪♪

29:15.545 --> 29:16.713
Celina!

29:16.713 --> 29:24.846
♪♪

29:24.846 --> 29:27.808
7-Adam-15, I have an officer
down and another one missing.

29:27.808 --> 29:29.726
[ Radio static crackles ]

29:29.726 --> 29:31.311
7-Adam-15?

29:31.311 --> 29:32.604
[ Radio static crackles ]

29:32.604 --> 29:34.856
♪♪

29:34.856 --> 29:36.525
7-Adam-15, I have
priority traffic.

29:36.525 --> 29:38.860
Be smart.

29:38.860 --> 29:39.945
Just keep moving...
Dispatch: <i>All units clear</i>
<i>the air for priority traffic.</i>

29:39.945 --> 29:41.446
...and everything will be fine.
<i>Adam-15 go.</i>

29:41.446 --> 29:43.031
Nolan: <i>I can't raise</i>
<i>Officer Juarez on the radio.</i>

29:43.031 --> 29:45.033
<i>She may have been 2-0-7'd</i>
<i>but still in the hospital.</i>

29:45.033 --> 29:46.243
<i>I need additional units</i>
<i>to help search.</i>

29:46.243 --> 29:47.244
Turn that off.

29:47.244 --> 29:49.079
I said turn it off!
Celina: I did.

29:49.079 --> 29:51.206
<i>Where are we going?</i>
<i>To the ambulance bay?</i>

29:51.206 --> 29:52.624
<i>Just shut up</i>
<i>and keep moving.</i>

29:52.624 --> 29:57.546
♪♪

29:57.546 --> 29:59.131
Okay. Okay.

29:59.131 --> 30:01.591
Get in.
Get in.

30:01.591 --> 30:05.637
♪♪

30:05.637 --> 30:07.681
[ Groaning ]
Oh.

30:07.681 --> 30:09.141
[ Wincing ]

30:09.141 --> 30:10.225
Just give me a minute.

30:10.225 --> 30:11.601
Look, there's no
happy endings here.

30:11.601 --> 30:13.061
You know that, right?
Shut up.

30:13.061 --> 30:14.438
You need to get
your wounds treated.

30:14.438 --> 30:15.522
You should have
kidnapped a doctor.

30:15.522 --> 30:16.648
Shut up.

30:16.648 --> 30:18.150
I just need
to catch my breath.

30:18.150 --> 30:20.777
Let me at least take a look
at your wounds.

30:20.777 --> 30:22.195
Nice try.

30:22.195 --> 30:24.364
Look...

30:24.364 --> 30:27.284
police officers have a sworn
responsibility to render aid,

30:27.284 --> 30:28.243
even to people
trying to kill them.

30:30.120 --> 30:32.122
Lift your shirt.
Okay.

30:32.122 --> 30:33.457
[ Groaning ]

30:33.457 --> 30:35.208
All righty.

30:35.208 --> 30:39.004
♪♪

30:39.004 --> 30:41.548
[ Muffled ]
Okay. Uh...

30:41.548 --> 30:43.508
Listen.
You need this.

30:43.508 --> 30:45.093
Okay?
These are antibiotics.

30:45.093 --> 30:46.011
You can see the label
right there.

30:46.011 --> 30:47.387
Oh, forget it.
We gotta go.

30:47.387 --> 30:48.847
It'll just take
two seconds.

30:48.847 --> 30:50.557
And your wounds are definitely
infected by this point.

30:50.557 --> 30:51.600
Just let me do this.

30:51.600 --> 30:54.519
Okay. Okay.

30:54.519 --> 30:55.520
Come on.
Okay.

30:55.520 --> 30:57.147
Let's go.
Okay.

30:59.399 --> 31:01.651
Let me see.

31:01.651 --> 31:04.821
[ Whimpers ]

31:04.821 --> 31:06.114
Okay.

31:06.114 --> 31:08.116
Now you're gonna
drive us out of here.

31:08.116 --> 31:09.117
Let's go.

31:09.117 --> 31:11.620
Okay. All righty.

31:11.620 --> 31:20.087
♪♪

31:20.087 --> 31:21.296
[ Gunshot ricochets]

31:21.296 --> 31:22.672
Aah!
Whoa!

31:22.672 --> 31:31.807
♪♪

31:31.807 --> 31:32.808
What are you doing?

31:32.808 --> 31:33.767
Just give it a second.

31:35.894 --> 31:37.270
Give what a second?

31:38.855 --> 31:40.190
How did you manage that?

31:40.190 --> 31:42.234
I showed him
the antibiotic,

31:42.234 --> 31:44.778
but then with a little
sleight of hand, morphine.

31:44.778 --> 31:46.446
Impressive.

31:46.446 --> 31:48.240
My sister and I used to do
these little magic shows.

31:49.491 --> 31:50.534
I'll bet
they were amazing.

31:50.534 --> 31:51.910
It was.

31:52.994 --> 31:54.496
Should be good to go.

31:54.496 --> 32:04.381
♪♪

32:11.263 --> 32:12.973
Am I under arrest?

32:12.973 --> 32:14.891
Depends.
You got a permit?

32:15.892 --> 32:17.894
Yeah.

32:17.894 --> 32:19.688
Back at the house.

32:19.688 --> 32:21.356
What are you doing here,
Benny?

32:21.356 --> 32:24.693
Are you asking as a cop
or as my sister?

32:24.693 --> 32:26.194
I'm asking as a sister.

32:26.194 --> 32:28.029
I'm listening as a cop.

32:30.615 --> 32:32.826
I bought some stocks
on a margin.

32:32.826 --> 32:34.411
The stocks went south.

32:34.411 --> 32:36.538
Margin got called.

32:36.538 --> 32:37.664
I didn't have it.

32:37.664 --> 32:38.874
How much?

32:38.874 --> 32:41.042
500 grand.
Hmm.

32:42.669 --> 32:44.713
I sold everything
I could get my hands on.

32:44.713 --> 32:46.131
I was still a hundred short.

32:46.131 --> 32:47.924
So you went
to a loan shark?

32:47.924 --> 32:50.427
I know I screwed up.
I can fix it.

32:50.427 --> 32:52.095
No.

32:52.095 --> 32:53.889
You're gonna
let us handle it.

32:53.889 --> 32:56.641
What is this loan shark's name,
and where can we find him?

32:56.641 --> 33:00.937
♪♪

33:00.937 --> 33:02.689
Anyone ever tell you
not to lend to a guy

33:02.689 --> 33:05.066
whose sister
is a cop?

33:05.066 --> 33:07.277
[ Chuckles ]
Detectives.

33:07.277 --> 33:09.237
I haven't done
anything illegal.

33:09.237 --> 33:12.490
Just a legitimate loan
to a guy who's down on his luck.

33:12.490 --> 33:14.075
Well, your legitimate
collection agent

33:14.075 --> 33:15.577
landed my mom
in the hospital.

33:15.577 --> 33:16.995
Emilia wasn't kidding
when she said

33:16.995 --> 33:18.288
she got you
with her purse.

33:18.288 --> 33:20.207
You are under arrest
for assault,

33:20.207 --> 33:23.001
with an enhancement
for elder abuse.

33:23.001 --> 33:24.878
Don't mess with the Lopez women.
It doesn't end well.

33:29.382 --> 33:31.176
[ Monitor beeping ]

33:39.976 --> 33:42.604
The doctor said they got
the bullet fragment.

33:44.064 --> 33:46.566
There's nothing
to worry about.

33:46.566 --> 33:47.525
That's great.

33:47.525 --> 33:49.527
[ Winces ]

33:49.527 --> 33:52.030
I never thought I'd be so happy
to feel pain in my life.

33:55.659 --> 33:57.452
You okay?

33:57.452 --> 33:59.162
No.

34:01.248 --> 34:04.000
There's something
I have to tell you.

34:04.000 --> 34:05.919
Ash...

34:05.919 --> 34:09.631
I spent my whole life
worrying about my dad.

34:09.631 --> 34:13.176
If he was late
getting home,

34:13.176 --> 34:14.844
Mom would pretend
everything was fine,

34:14.844 --> 34:18.098
but I know
she was terrified.

34:18.098 --> 34:20.684
When I saw you wheeled
into surgery,

34:20.684 --> 34:24.104
I realized...

34:24.104 --> 34:26.773
I can't do that again.

34:28.316 --> 34:31.361
Are -- Are y-you
breaking up with me?

34:35.740 --> 34:37.784
I'm sorry.

34:39.035 --> 34:40.620
I just got out of surgery.

34:40.620 --> 34:43.623
I know.

34:43.623 --> 34:47.210
I thought I'd get it in
before the anesthesia wore off.

34:47.210 --> 34:49.421
[ Chuckles ]

34:49.421 --> 34:52.674
I...still love you.

34:52.674 --> 34:57.971
I'll probably be in love with
you for longer than I'd like.

34:57.971 --> 35:01.474
And if there was any chance
you were going to retire...

35:01.474 --> 35:07.063
♪♪

35:07.063 --> 35:09.190
I know.
[ Sighs ]

35:11.109 --> 35:12.652
Can I get you anything?

35:12.652 --> 35:15.363
♪♪

35:15.363 --> 35:17.407
No.

35:17.407 --> 35:21.786
Okay.
I'll go, then.

35:23.538 --> 35:29.169
♪♪

35:29.169 --> 35:31.379
[ Breathes shakily ]

35:31.379 --> 35:37.761
♪♪

35:37.761 --> 35:39.471
[ Sighs deeply ]

35:39.471 --> 35:41.306
So, now how do you feel
about hospitals?

35:41.306 --> 35:43.558
I love them.
[ Chuckles ]

35:43.558 --> 35:44.851
Nah, today was great.
Nurse: You're good to go.

35:44.851 --> 35:46.853
Thank you very much.
Thank you.

35:46.853 --> 35:49.773
You know, that, uh,
morphine move was very smart.

35:49.773 --> 35:50.774
I would not have
thought of that.

35:50.774 --> 35:52.776
Thank you.
Uh...

35:52.776 --> 35:54.736
What is it?

35:54.736 --> 35:55.987
Oh, you're gonna
think I'm crazy.

35:55.987 --> 35:57.030
No, never.

35:57.030 --> 35:58.907
It was my sister's idea.

35:58.907 --> 36:00.617
Oh.
Mm.

36:00.617 --> 36:04.537
As in you saw her or...?

36:04.537 --> 36:06.498
No.

36:06.498 --> 36:07.499
I can't really explain it.

36:07.499 --> 36:09.459
I-I feel like
she was with me.

36:09.459 --> 36:10.585
It's weird.

36:10.585 --> 36:13.797
Oh, well, I think that's
a -- a lovely thought,

36:13.797 --> 36:16.716
as long as there were no,
you know,

36:16.716 --> 36:18.009
auditory hallucinations --

36:18.009 --> 36:19.177
No.
I had to ask.

36:19.177 --> 36:20.095
[ Chuckles ]

36:21.721 --> 36:24.516
[ Telephone ringing,
cellphone buzzing ]

36:24.516 --> 36:26.017
Oh.

36:26.017 --> 36:27.268
Uh, Watch Commander's office.

36:27.268 --> 36:29.145
Sergeant Grey is unavailable.

36:29.145 --> 36:30.730
End of shift is denied and --

36:30.730 --> 36:33.233
[ Line beeping,
cellphone ringing ]

36:33.233 --> 36:34.275
Sgt. Grey:
Hey, there you are.

36:34.275 --> 36:35.944
I was just calling.

36:35.944 --> 36:36.778
Hey.

36:36.778 --> 36:38.697
So, how'd it go?

36:38.697 --> 36:40.031
It was great.

36:40.031 --> 36:42.075
It was...
[ Both laugh ]

36:42.075 --> 36:44.452
I just spoke with
the Communications Supervisor.

36:44.452 --> 36:48.164
Said you did a masterful job
managing calls

36:48.164 --> 36:49.499
with half
the normal staff.

36:49.499 --> 36:51.626
Hmm. [ Exhales sharply ]
Thank you.

36:51.626 --> 36:54.295
I am so ready to give you
your job back.

36:54.295 --> 36:55.797
[ Chuckles ]

36:55.797 --> 36:57.173
Understood.

36:57.173 --> 36:59.008
Good night, sir.
Good night.

36:59.008 --> 37:00.969
Oh, uh, how was
Tim's laparoscopic?

37:02.846 --> 37:06.349
Yeah. Um...

37:06.349 --> 37:08.893
He ended up needing
emergency spinal surgery.

37:12.021 --> 37:17.152
[ <i>Indistinct page</i>
<i>over intercom</i> ]

37:17.152 --> 37:19.946
[ Indistinct conversations ]

37:19.946 --> 37:21.906
[ Monitor beeping ]

37:21.906 --> 37:23.199
Are you okay?

37:23.199 --> 37:24.367
Uh, why didn't
anyone tell me?

37:24.367 --> 37:26.828
No, I'm -- I'm good.
I'm good.

37:26.828 --> 37:30.165
Doctor said I'm gonna
make a full recovery.

37:30.165 --> 37:33.293
And I told everyone
to keep you in the dark.

37:33.293 --> 37:34.669
Why?

37:34.669 --> 37:35.712
I didn't want
you to worry.

37:38.757 --> 37:40.508
So, just to be clear --

37:40.508 --> 37:41.718
You thought you might
be paralyzed,

37:41.718 --> 37:43.178
but you were
worried about <i>me?</i>

37:43.178 --> 37:44.471
You know what?
Slow your roll, Chen.

37:44.471 --> 37:46.097
[ Stammers, sighs ]

37:46.097 --> 37:49.017
Clearly, I misspoke.
I was worried about the station.

37:49.017 --> 37:51.728
And I knew you'd be
too concerned about me

37:51.728 --> 37:54.105
to take over for Smitty.

37:54.105 --> 37:56.191
Mm-hmm.

37:56.191 --> 37:58.359
I heard you saved the day,
though.

37:58.359 --> 38:00.111
Being sergeant's
not so hard.

38:00.111 --> 38:01.988
I don't know why
you're always complaining.

38:01.988 --> 38:05.200
Really?
Just smooth sailing?

38:05.200 --> 38:07.619
No. It was awful.

38:07.619 --> 38:09.537
How do that many things
go wrong in one day?

38:09.537 --> 38:11.414
That wasn't even
a particularly bad day.

38:11.414 --> 38:13.625
[ Chuckles ]

38:13.625 --> 38:15.335
Where's Ashley?

38:15.335 --> 38:17.796
Yeah, I-I, uh --
I sent her home.

38:17.796 --> 38:19.631
She was exhausted.

38:19.631 --> 38:21.424
Okay. Hm.

38:22.842 --> 38:24.385
[ Exhales sharply ]

38:24.385 --> 38:26.054
What are you doing?

38:27.764 --> 38:30.266
I'm keeping you company.

38:30.266 --> 38:31.810
[ Scoffs ]

38:31.810 --> 38:33.353
You don't have
to do that.

38:33.353 --> 38:34.521
I know.

38:34.521 --> 38:38.483
♪♪

38:38.483 --> 38:42.153
Lopez: Okay, okay.
[ Laughter ]

38:42.153 --> 38:43.321
-Oh, okay.
-Just open it.

38:43.321 --> 38:45.698
-Sure. Okay.
-He's fine. He's fine.

38:45.698 --> 38:48.993
Okay, so and then the door
opens, and Wesley walks in

38:48.993 --> 38:50.703
to represent me.
[ All chuckling ]

38:50.703 --> 38:52.247
All of us.

38:52.247 --> 38:53.456
I thought Angela's head
was going to explode.

38:53.456 --> 38:54.874
[ Laughter ]

38:54.874 --> 38:56.918
Good man, looking out for
your brothers-in-law.

38:56.918 --> 38:58.753
Whoa.
Good man?

38:58.753 --> 39:00.505
<i>Brave</i> man.
Wesley: No, no, no, no.

39:00.505 --> 39:02.173
No, no, no, no.
Not -- Not so brave.

39:02.173 --> 39:04.384
I knew that
she would understand.

39:04.384 --> 39:07.595
Angela believes
in tough love, sure.

39:07.595 --> 39:10.515
But no one is more protective
of the people she cares about.

39:10.515 --> 39:11.724
Oh.

39:11.724 --> 39:13.017
♪♪

39:13.017 --> 39:14.352
I have something to say.

39:14.352 --> 39:16.396
Mom, you don't have to.
Yes, I do.

39:16.396 --> 39:20.525
It's something I should have
said a long time ago to you.

39:20.525 --> 39:22.110
I know you always thought

39:22.110 --> 39:25.321
I didn't pay you
enough attention growing up,

39:25.321 --> 39:28.658
that all my focus
went to your brothers.

39:28.658 --> 39:32.078
I always denied it,
but you were right.

39:32.078 --> 39:35.331
It's not because
I didn't <i>love</i> you as much.

39:38.167 --> 39:41.880
You're my daughter,
my only daughter,

39:41.880 --> 39:46.175
and I love you in a way
that is only for you.

39:46.175 --> 39:47.635
♪ Yeah, I don't care now ♪

39:47.635 --> 39:52.974
But you didn't need me
as much as much.

39:52.974 --> 39:55.560
Not the way they did.
[ Chuckles ]

39:55.560 --> 39:59.856
Since you could crawl,
you took care of yourself.

39:59.856 --> 40:02.984
And when you could walk,
you took care of your brothers,

40:02.984 --> 40:05.111
even though they were
older than you.

40:05.111 --> 40:09.991
And I relied on you.
I came to expect it.

40:09.991 --> 40:12.368
[ Voice breaking ]
But as strong as you were,

40:12.368 --> 40:15.955
I should have realized that
you still needed your mother.

40:15.955 --> 40:18.041
♪ The world got cold ♪

40:18.041 --> 40:23.129
I love you, mija.

40:23.129 --> 40:24.547
And I'm sorry.

40:24.547 --> 40:26.549
♪ I'm less afraid ♪

40:26.549 --> 40:27.759
To Angela.

40:27.759 --> 40:28.927
Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

40:28.927 --> 40:30.178
-To Angela.
-Salud.

40:30.178 --> 40:31.429
[ Bottles clinking ]
All: Salud.

40:31.429 --> 40:33.973
Mom, I love you.
[ Chuckles ]

40:33.973 --> 40:35.558
♪ Go tumbling ♪

40:35.558 --> 40:36.559
Thank you.

40:36.559 --> 40:38.269
♪ Let the ghost get loud ♪

40:38.269 --> 40:40.521
Are you still worried
I went back too soon?

40:40.521 --> 40:44.359
No. Actually, you seemed
pretty amazing today.

40:44.359 --> 40:45.401
[ Chuckles ]

40:45.401 --> 40:46.736
I guess the only
question left is,

40:46.736 --> 40:47.946
are you ever gonna
fill me in

40:47.946 --> 40:49.864
on the whole
"I was dead before" thing?

40:49.864 --> 40:51.491
Well,
there's not much to tell.

40:51.491 --> 40:53.493
You already know about
the second time --

40:53.493 --> 40:56.579
My oxygen regulator
malfunctioned on a halo jump.

40:56.579 --> 40:59.791
Luckily, the other guys noticed,
pulled my ripcord,

40:59.791 --> 41:03.294
and brought me back to life
on the ground.

41:03.294 --> 41:06.089
That is so badass.
[ Chuckles ]

41:06.089 --> 41:07.090
And the first time?

41:07.090 --> 41:09.425
Two words -- Big Foot.

41:09.425 --> 41:10.593
See, I don't even know
why I bother.

41:10.593 --> 41:11.719
[ Chuckles ]

41:11.719 --> 41:12.887
'Cause you love me.
Fair enough.

41:12.887 --> 41:16.557
[ Laughs ]

41:16.557 --> 41:20.436
You know, the first two times
I was brought back to life,

41:20.436 --> 41:25.024
I was scared,
but only a little.

41:25.024 --> 41:27.944
And I moved on
pretty quickly.

41:27.944 --> 41:31.406
But this --
this last time,

41:31.406 --> 41:35.243
all I could think about
was losing you.

41:35.243 --> 41:38.371
I've never
been happier

41:38.371 --> 41:42.875
or felt
more seen or loved.

41:42.875 --> 41:45.586
And the thought
of losing a second

41:45.586 --> 41:49.090
of whatever time we have left
was heartbreaking.

41:50.925 --> 41:54.303
So here's my question.

41:56.180 --> 41:58.975
John Nolan...

41:58.975 --> 42:00.226
will you marry me?

42:00.226 --> 42:02.478
♪ As long as you're with me ♪

42:02.478 --> 42:04.647
♪ As long as you're with me ♪

42:04.647 --> 42:06.649
Try and stop me.

42:06.649 --> 42:08.568
♪ As long as you're with me ♪

42:08.568 --> 42:10.903
♪ Not scared of no trouble ♪

42:10.903 --> 42:11.904
[ Laughs ]

42:16.993 --> 42:19.996
-- Captions by VITAC --

42:19.996 --> 42:28.379
♪♪

42:28.379 --> 42:36.512
♪♪

42:36.512 --> 42:44.937
♪♪
